Class Controller

  • java.lang.Object
    • Controller
  • public class Controller
extends java.lang.Object
    A controller class that acts as a link between the view, model and database in this project. This class calls methods in the EntryManager (the model), View (the view) and MySQLHandler (the database connection) classes to transfer data between them. For example, the controller handles all listeners on the view to more easily be able to transfer the data in the view to the model.

      • Controller

        public Controller​(EntryManager em,
                  View v,
                  FileIO f,
                  MySQLHandler m)
        Creates a new Controller that can read and write data from files as well as a MySQL database and pass data between a model and a view.
        Parameters:
        em - The model the controller will interact with.
        v - The view the controller will interact with.
        f - The file input-output handler that the model will use to write data to files.
        m - The database handler the controller will use to manage reads and writes to the database.
